{"arkId":"cl010093350","url":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010093350","modified ":"2026-02-28","title":"La Vierge et l\u0027Enfant tenant un phylact\u00e8re","titleComplement":"","denominationTitle":[{"type":"Titre","value":"La Vierge et l\u0027Enfant tenant un phylact\u00e8re"}],"displayDateCreated":"Date de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication : 1450 - 1475","currentLocation":"Richelieu, [SCULPT] Salle 210 - Le tombeau de Philippe Pot - La sculpture gothique au 15e si\u00e8cle : Paris, la Bourgogne","room":"Salle 210, Aile Aile Richelieu, Niveau 0","isMuseesNationauxRecuperation":false,"dateCreated":[{"startYear":1450,"endYear":1475,"imprecision":"","text":"3e quart du XVe si\u00e8cle","type":"Date de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication","doubt":""}],"creator":[{"label":"France Bourgogne","attributionLevel":"Attribution actuelle","linkType":"","creatorRole":"","authenticationType":"","doubt":"","attributedBy":"","attributedYear":"","wikidata":""}],"objectNumber":[{"value":"RF 940","type":"Num\u00e9ro principal"}],"collection":"D\u00e9partement des Sculptures du Moyen Age, de la Renaissance et des temps modernes","printsDrawingsEntity":"","printsDrawingsCollection":"","objectType":"statue","originalObject":"","printState":"","description":"","inscriptions":"Inscription : \r ; CEUX QUI (La plus r\u00e9cente en capitales)\r ; QU(i (?)) SEQUITur (Sur le phylact\u00e8re, deux inscriptions peintes, superpos\u00e9es, incompl\u00e8tes et en majeure partie illisibles. El\u00e9ments assur\u00e9s de la plus ancienne, en caract\u00e8res gothiques)","namesAndTitles":"","onomastics":"","dimension":[{"type":"Hauteur","value":"0,96","displayDimension":"0,96 m","unit":"m","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":1,"note":""},{"type":"Largeur","value":"0,25","displayDimension":"0,25 m","unit":"m","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":2,"note":""},{"type":"Profondeur","value":"0,44","displayDimension":"0,44 m","unit":"m","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPr